                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-91-off528 t18320906-91-crimeloc530"></join>. On the 15th of September, 1831, the prisoner came to his shop to me, and said he came from Mr. Embleton, to borrow a pair of stocks and dies, as he had a job to do for Mr. Magnay; I knew Mr. Embleton to be a customer, and though the prisoner was a stranger, I let him have the articles, as I believed he came with a true story.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Do you mean to say I asked you for these things? A. Yes, you asked for them - it was not my Mistress asked me.</p>
